<TITLE> Rough weather in North Bay of Bengal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 22 (bdnews24.com)  Squally weather is likely over the North Bay of Bengal and adjoining coastal areas of Bangladesh due to a deep convection over the area, the meteorological department said on Saturday. The North Bay will remain rough. Maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla have been asked to keep hoisted local cautionary signal number three. All fishing boats and trawlers over North Bay have been advised to remain in shelter until further notice
